<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4764054>
        a                        fabio:Figure ;
        dc:description           "Figs. 5-6. Adult male characters of Isoperla denningi, San Mateo Cr., San Diego Co., CA, and I. fulva, Sand Cr., Larimer Co., CO & Pole Cr., Juab Co., UT, 32-50x. Fig. 5a. I. denningi aedeagus, lateral; sclerotized process (arrow & inset-lateral view). Lobes A-B: posterobasal, C: posteroapical, D: dorsolateral pair. Fig. 5b. Aedeagus, ventral; sclerotized process (arrow & inset-posterior view). Fig. 5c. Paraprocts (arrow). Fig. 5d. Vesicle. Fig. 6a. I.fulva aedeagus, lateral; sclerotized process (left white arrow & inset-lateral view); spinule patch (right white arrow & inset); paraprocts (inset-black arrow). Lobes A: posterior, B: dorsal, C: anterior. Fig. 6b. Aedeagus, ventral; sclerotized process (arrow & inset-posterior view). Fig. 6c. Aedeagus, dorsal; sclerotized process (black arrow); spinule patch (white arrow). Fig. 6d. Vesicle." ;
        fabio:hasRepresentation  "https://zenodo.org/record/4764054/files/figure.png" .
